Can you write a MATLAB code that generates a table with the name of three basic styles of art and their brief description?
Here's the code:
style_names = {'Realism', 'Impressionism', 'Abstract'};
style_description = {'Realism refers to the depiction of objects as they appear in reality, without distortion or stylization.', 'Impressionism is characterized by relatively small, thin, yet visible brush strokes, open composition, emphasis on accurate depiction of light in its changing qualities', 'Abstract art is a style of art that emphasizes form, color, and line, often with little to no attempt at representing the physical world realistically.'};
art_styles = table(style_names', style_description', 'VariableNames', {'Art Style', 'Description'});
Can you please confirm if this meets your requirement?
